Generate Nonparametric Bootstrap Samples

xstar_nb.Rd

Generate Nonparametric Bootstrap Samples

xstar_nb(x, bcap = 5000L, seed = NULL)

Arguments

x

Matrix, data frame, or vector. Sample data.
bcap

Integer. Number of bootstrap samples.
seed

Integer. Random seed.

Value

Returns the same data type as input data.

Dependencies

  • rmvn_chol() (test)

See also

Other Nonparametric Bootstrap Functions: ci_bca_helper(), ci_bca(), ci_bc(), ci_pc(), func_jackknife(), func_thetahatstar_nb(), func_xstar_nb(), jackknife(), thetahatstar_nb()

Author

Ivan Jacob Agaloos Pesigan

Examples

x <- rnorm(n = 100)
xstar_nb(x, bcap = 5L)
